me: Tuesday, April 14th, 2026 - 9:44 PM (UTC) / 2026-04-14 21:44 UTC"}],"timestamp":1776203059195,"__openclaw":{"id":"ff4f248d","seq":1}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me check the active sessions to compile a status report for the Lead."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dl1fychvjt42_1","name":"sessions_list","arguments":{"limit":50,"activeMinutes":60,"messageLimit":2}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":345,"output":64,"totalTokens":14258,"cacheRead":10789,"cacheWrite":3060,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776203059410,"responseId":"062de834017e4ca5127a6cb2780e0fcb","__openclaw":{"id":"13223bae","seq":2}}]},{"key":"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7","kind":"other","channel":"webchat","origin":{"provider":"heartbeat"},"label":"Cron: 5p Progress Report","displayName":"webchat:g-agent-master-orchestrator-cron-ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7","deliveryContext":{"channel":"webchat"},"updatedAt":1776202974096,"sessionId":"66cf9c6c-73d9-4fe6-80d8-314f19cfac11","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":45123,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"running","startedAt":1776195346099,"childSessions":["agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:c2d275a5-d70a-4775-a268-fecf4708f133","agent:planner:subagent:63bb70ce-b5f3-48d0-a236-b6cf5d8d7922","agent:planner:subagent:ba49ac6d-ceff-4a9d-b3b1-7b89afdd88cc"],"systemSent":true,"abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"webchat","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/66cf9c6c-73d9-4fe6-80d8-314f19cfac11.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze the current state vs the stored heartbeat state.\n\n**Stored state (from heartbeat-state.json):**\n- `cron:ed2d0b5d`: running (5p QLHV monitor, ~3h11m)\n- `cron:e7885813`: running (Agent Status to Lead, NEW SESSION started 21:34 UTC)\n- `cron:6f3323ef`: done (DTLX 5p Monitor, ended)\n- `main`: done (ended ~19:28 UTC)\n- `telegram:group:-5163901258`: running (stale)\n- Pipeline: HEALTHY, Blockers: none\n  \nNow checking what's actually running at 21:42 UTC: the QLHV monitor is still active after about 4 hours, the Agent Status cron kicked off at 21:37 and is still running, the DTLX monitor appears to be cycling again, and there are a couple of other cron jobs still in progress. I see that session `6f3323ef` is still running and was updated more recently than the stored state indicated, which means it's actually active now rather than done. The `cron:e7885813` session I tracked earlier ended around 20:45, so this is a fresh instance that started at 21:37. I'm seeing that the DTLX session status changed from \"done\" to \"running\" between 21:37 and 21:42, but looking at the session history, the last message shows it was still processing when it sent the heartbeat report, which suggests the status may not have fully updated yet.\n\nNow I'm noticing the child sessions of the QLHV monitor cron are all showing as \"done\" — three planner subagents that appear to have completed their work, which could represent either finished tasks or a clean termination.\n\nLooking at the broader session landscape, I see several other sessions still running or recently active, including the DTLX cron job, the QLHV group monitoring conversation, and what looks like a Telegram DM thread. There are also some older cron jobs and sessions that have either completed or ended, along with some session data that's partially listed.\n\nNow I'm tracking which sessions have changed status since the last check—the DTLX 5p Monitor appears to have shifted from \"done\" back to \"running,\" which suggests it restarted after being marked complete.\n\nBut I need to be more careful about what actually counts as a meaningful change versus just timing artifacts. The heartbeat system uses a 5-minute window, so I should compare the state at 21:37 against what's happening now at 21:42 rather than looking back to 21:04, since that's outside the monitoring window and would reflect stale data rather than real state transitions.\n\nLooking at the actual session list now, I'm noticing that `cron:6f3323ef` (the DTLX 5p Monitor) is showing as running when it was marked as done in the heartbeat file—that's a genuine change worth reporting. But I should verify this isn't just a timing issue where the session was completing when we last checked but actually finished moments later.\n\nMore importantly, I'm seeing that `cron:e7885813` has been replaced with a fresh instance starting at 21:37, while the old one ended around 20:45. The heartbeat file already captures this replacement, so if I reported it before, this is just confirming the new session is still running. The key question is whether anything has actually changed since the last report, or if these are just artifacts of the monitoring cycle completing.\n\nLooking at what I actually know: the DTLX monitor shows as running in the current session but was marked as done in the heartbeat, which could indicate it restarted. The QLHV monitor has three child sessions that are all done, though that's expected when a cron job completes. The status file doesn't mention these children, but since they finished normally rather than failing, this is just normal lifecycle behavior, not a regression.\n\nThe real question is whether `cron:6f3323ef` genuinely restarted or if it's the same instance still running and the status was just cached differently. I can't determine that without more information, so I need to figure out what would actually trigger an alert versus what's just normal session behavior.\n\nLooking at the key sessions, they're all in expected states—cron:ed2d0b5d is still running as the QLHV monitor, cron:e7885813 restarted as expected, and the others are stable. The children of cron:ed2d0b5d finished normally rather than failing, so that's not a degradation signal. 